					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not a very good programmer, so take this advice with a grain of salt, but I think it's way better to work on something you actually want to work on.  Grab an assembler, head on over to the Nerdy Nights Tutorials and open up a browser page to 6502 opcodes and have at it.  Blargg's NES tutorials are pretty handy references to have too.
<br />
<br />If you decide you want to start with a higher level language to grasp the concepts I'd go with something simple.  You probably want your first program to be one file and easy for you to follow and understand.
<br />
<br />But seriously, you want to work on the NES, so work on the NES.</div>

